England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Skilling","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and English: habitational name from Skelling in Skirwith (Cumberland), probably from Old Norse <i>skáli</i> ‘shieling, temporary hut’ + <i>eng</i> ‘meadow, pasture’.","Scottish and English: from the Old English personal name <i>Scilling</i>, in a Scandinavianized form unrecorded in Middle English or Older Scots.","English: possibly a Scots variant of   Shilling  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Skillin","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Skilling  ."]},{"name":"Shilling","meanings":["English: nickname from the Middle English coin name <i>schilling</i> ‘shilling’ (Old English <i>scilling</i>), probably referring to a fee or rent owed or paid. In addition, the name may also arise from an unrecorded Middle English personal name <i>Shilling</i> (Old English <i>Scilling</i>), from the word above. Compare   Farthing  ,   Grote  ,   Halfpenny  , and   Penny  .","English: perhaps sometimes a variant of   Sellen  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of   Schilling  ."]},{"name":"Skillings","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Skilling  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Skillen","meanings":["English and Scottish (Ayrshire):","variant of   Skilling  .","variant of   Skillern  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Skilling was born in 1415, in England, United Kingdom. She married John Dale about 1440, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1415–":"1415–Surnud","1415–1479":"1415–1479","1443–1514":"1443–1514","1415–Female":"1415–Surnud","1415":"1415","1514":"1514","1479":"1479","1443":"1443","about 1440":"umbes 1440","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1415–":"1415–Kuollut","1415–1479":"1415–1479","1443–1514":"1443–1514","1415–Female":"1415–Kuollut","1415":"1415","1514":"1514","1479":"1479","1443":"1443","about 1440":"noin 1440","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1415–":"1415–Décédée","1415–1479":"1415–1479","1443–1514":"1443–1514","1415–Female":"1415–Décédée","1415":"1415","1514":"1514","1479":"1479","1443":"1443","about 1440":"environ 1440","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Alice Skilling est née en 1415, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé John Dale environ 1440, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1415–":"1415–Verstorben","1415–1479":"1415–1479","1443–1514":"1443–1514","1415–Female":"1415–Verstorben","1415":"1415","1514":"1514","1479":"1479","1443":"1443","about 1440":"um 1440","England":"England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Alice Skilling wurde 1415 in England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat um 1440 in England, United Kingdom John Dale geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1415–":"1415–Desede","1415–1479":"1415–1479","1443–1514":"1443–1514","1415